On International Women's Day, the article discusses the importance of recognizing and celebrating the achievements of women and girls in the United States and around the world. The author emphasizes the commitment of the Administration to invest in the opportunity, security, and wellbeing of women. This includes the establishment of the White House Gender Policy Council and the goal of ensuring equal representation of women at all levels of the federal government. The article acknowledges the historical struggles and contributions of women, while also highlighting the systemic obstacles that hinder gender equality. It recognizes the significant role women have played in responding to the global pandemic, including as vaccine researchers, healthcare workers, and essential workers. However, it also mentions the negative impact of the pandemic on women's economic gains, education, and increased incidents of violence against women. The article concludes by emphasizing the importance of elevating the status of women and girls globally, as it leads to a more just, fair, and prosperous world.